    <sec>
      <title>BayMeth: A Bayesian framework for translating read densities into methylation levels</title>
      <p>DNAme data can be obtained using MBD-seq or a similar affinity enrichment assay. Let <italic>y</italic><sub><italic>iS</italic></sub> and <italic>y</italic><sub><italic>iC</italic></sub> denote the observed number of (uniquely) mapped reads for genomic regions <italic>i</italic> = 1, …, <italic>n</italic> for the sample of interest and the SssI control, respectively. Throughout this paper, we use non-overlapping regions (mostly of width 100bp) that have at least 75% mappable bases (see Materials and methods). Let </p>
