        <p> Notably, <monospace>p</monospace>(<italic>y</italic><sub><italic>iS</italic></sub>, <italic>y</italic><sub><italic>iC</italic></sub>) can be calculated analytically [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B34">34</xref>], so that the marginal posterior distribution: </p>
